            . I <rs id="t18321018-210-viclabel1167" type="occupation">keep a shoe-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-210-victim1832 t18321018-210-viclabel1167"></join>, at <placeName id="t18321018-210-crimeloc1168">Chelsea</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-210-crimeloc1168" type="placeName" value="Chelsea"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-210-crimeloc1168" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-210-off1165 t18321018-210-crimeloc1168"></join>. I lost two pairs of shoes on the 8th of October, while I was out.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-210-person1834">
                  HANNAH 
                  INCE
               <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1834" type="surname" value="INCE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1834" type="given" value="HANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1834" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with my aunt, the prosecutrix. On the 8th of October the shoes were lost, but I did not know who took them; I was told they were taken.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-210-person1835">
                  JOSEPH 
                  WILKINS
               <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1835" type="surname" value="WILKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1835" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1835" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable B 100). Between seven and eight o'clock on the 8th of October, Goose and I were coming up the King's-road, and saw the two prisoners near the prosecutrix's house; we watched them -Marriott came from the door with something, which he showed to Wren; it appeared like the shoes: they all walked away - there were four of them together; we followed them to the other side of Sloane-square, and there I caught hold of Marriott - he sprung into the road, and threw something from him; I pursued, but he got into a court - we afterwards found him; this wire and this purse were found on him - the shoes were found thrown down an area.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-210-person1836">
                  EDWARD 
                  WEATHERLEY
               <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1836" type="surname" value="WEATHERLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1836" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1836" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable B 20). I went on the beat at nine o'clock; my brother officer told me that something was thrown away - I went the next morning, and found the shoes down the area.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-210-person1837">
                  ROBERT 
                  GOOSE
               <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1837" type="surname" value="GOOSE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1837" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-210-person1837" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable R 55). I was with the other officer, and saw Marriott come from the prosecutrix's door; go to Wren, and show him something - they ran off, and we followed them; I found one shoe in another area - I took Wren, but nothing was found on him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Marriott's Defence. I was running home, and this man called Stop thief! I had not been near the shop.</p>


